Joseph BYRNES, Appellant, v. Joseph W. SANFORD, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Atlanta, Georgia, Appellee. No. 9392. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. March 13, 1940. Joseph Byrnes, in pro per. Lawrence S. Camp, U. S.- Atty., and Harvey H. Tisinger and Jas. T. Manning, Asst. U. S. Attys., all of Atlanta, Ga., for appel-lee.

Before SIBLEY, HUTCHESON, and McCORD, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
